Summary of metrics for PolarSys projects

This document gathers the metrics retrieved on all analysed projects, summarises them, and proposes a transverse perspective on the various projects. Its main purpose is to compare the values of metrics, and thus help define and understand the thresholds used to compute the indicators.

This is a dynamically generated document: it takes as input the metrics.csv file generated by the dashboard and analyses and plots the values for all projects. In this very case, 11 projects with a total of 66 metrics have been analysed.

Rule-checking metrics

Rule-checking metrics are computed using two well-known open-source tools, PMD and FindBugs. These are executed by the Maturity Assessment process because a restricted set of the most harmful rules is used, instead of the default SonarQube quality profile. The list of rules checked can be found in the online documentation; only rules with a high priority are counted in the rating (i.e. < 4 for PMD and < 3 for FindBugs).
